com.xilinx.rapidwright.timing

Class TimingVertex

  • Object
    • com.xilinx.rapidwright.timing.TimingVertex

  • public class TimingVertex
extends Object
    A TimingVertex represents a node within the TimingGraph. It encapsulates slack, arrival time, required time, and whether it represents a pin on a flip flop.

    • Constructor Detail

      • TimingVertex

        public TimingVertex(String name)
        Creates a vertex for insertion into the TimingGraph.
        Parameters:
        name - Name is typically the hierarchical logical name of an input or output pin. In some cases this timing library is using the EDIFPortInst name for the name. This is noteworthy because the EDIFPortInst name may contain square brackets on pins that are indexed slices of a bus (for example some pins on CARRY8 have indices). The physical name for pins do not contain square brackets.

      • TimingVertex

        public TimingVertex(String name,
                    boolean isFlopInput)
        Create a timing vertex for insertion into the timing graph
        Parameters:
        name - - name is the cell name of an input or output pin
        isFlopInput - - to indicate if it is an input or output
